ZCZC OE98
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SATURDAY TO TUESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 172300 UTC
ON SATURDAY EVENING LOW PRESSURE CENTRES ARE EXP TO LIE OVER WALES AND
ICELAND. OVERNIGHT AND THROUGH SUNDAY THESE LOWS WILL MOV SLWY EWARDS AND
FILL AS PRESSURE BUILDS FM THE SW. BY MIDDAY ON MONDAY A TRANSIENT RIDGE
OF HIGH PRESSURE IS EXP ACROSS THE UK. THIS RIDGE WILL THEN COLLAPSE SEWARDS.
THERE IS THEN SOME SIG UNCERTAINTY HOWEVER LOW PRESSURE S OF ICELAND IS
CURRENTLY SIGNALLED TO MOV SEWARDS TO LIE ACROSS NERN IRELAND BY MIDDAY TUESDAY
BEFORE MOV E. ON SATURDAY EVENING STRG OR NEAR GALE FORCE WINDS ARE EXP ACROSS
THE W OF PORTPATRICK SPREADING E OVERNIGHT BEFORE EASING ON SUNDAY. ON
SUNDAY NIGHT GALE OR NEAR GALE FORCE WINDS WILL SPREAD IN FM THE W ACROSS
THE REGION. WINDS MAY TEMPO EASE ON MONDAY AFTERNOON BEFORE FURTHER GALES
SPREAD IN S OF 60 DEGREES N DURING THE EVENING POSSIBLY REACHING SEV GALE
IN PLACES. WINDS ARE LIKELY TO EASE FM THE NW ON TUESDAY
